%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22J.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer%20stifled%20a%20petition%20by%2070%20scientists%20beseeching%20President%20Truman%20not%20to%20use%20the%20atomic%20bomb.%20Read%20it%20here.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Physicist%20Leo%20Szilard%20stands%20before%20a%20blackboard%20indicating%20it%20with%20his%20hand%2C%20which%20is%20holding%20a%20piece%20of%20chalk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b1a6849751e300192a2fc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELeo%20Szilard%2C%20pictured%20circa%201945%2C%20circulated%20a%20petition%20to%20other%20Manhattan%20Project%20scientists%2C%20asking%20President%20Truman%20to%20reconsider%20using%20the%20atomic%20bomb%20on%20Japan.%3Cp%3EUniversal%20Images%20Group%20Editorial%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20August%201945%2C%20the%20US%20used%20atomic%20bombs%20on%20Japan%2C%20killing%20over%20100%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWeeks%20before%2C%20dozens%20of%20Manhattan%20Project%20scientists%20signed%20a%20petition%20opposing%20its%20use.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPresident%20Harry%20Truman%20never%20saw%20the%20petition%3B%20its%20existence%20remained%20a%20secret%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%206%20and%209%2C%201945%2C%20the%20United%20States%20dropped%20atomic%20bombs%20on%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki%2C%20Japan%2C%20killing%20at%20least%20100%2C000%20people%20instantly%20and%20thousands%20more%20from%20radiation%20illnesses%20and%20injuries%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuseum.archives.gov%2Ffeatured-document-display-atomic-bombing-hiroshima-and-nagasaki%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Archives%20Museum%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20weeks%20earlier%2C%20Leo%20Szilard%20and%20dozens%20of%20other%20scientists%20wh