%94%20that%20we%20have%20to%20rethink%20our%20ideas%20about%20the%20migration%20of%20humans%20to%20the%20Americas%2C%26quot%3B%20Mirian%20Liza%20Alves%20Forancelli%20Pacheco%2C%20study%20co-author%20and%20archaeologist%20at%20the%20Federal%20University%20of%20Sao%20Carlos%20in%20Brazil%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fgiant-sloths-early-people-americas-4c28e6d96f8bd58ede8ac48e0c39b533%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Associated%20Press.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20remains%20of%20the%20now-extinct%20giant%20sloth%20were%20discovered%20at%20the%20Santa%20Elina%20rock%20shelter%20in%20Brazil%2C%20and%20they%20included%20thousands%20of%20osteoderms%20%E2%80%94%20hard%20bony%20deposits%20that%20form%20within%20the%20skin%20of%20certain%20animals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Other%20giant%20ground%20sloth%20skeletons%20have%20been%20found%20in%20places%20like%20Daytona%20Beach%2C%20Florida.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b28df09751e300192a3a6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOther%20giant%20ground%20sloth%20skeletons%20have%20been%20found%20in%20places%20like%20Florida.%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Greenberg%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20three%20of%20the%20osteoderms%20appeared%20to%20have%20been%20polished%20and%20had%20holes%20drilled%20into%20them%2C%20suggesting%20humans%20had%20modified%20them%20into%20what%20was%20likely%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20ornaments%2C%26quot%3B%20researchers%20said.%20They%20added%20that%20the%20holes%20were%20not%20caused%20by%20natural%20abrasion%2C%20The%20AP%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20said%20that%20the%20pendants%20were%20made%20within%20days%20or%20a%20few%20years%20of%20the%20animal%20dying%2C%20the%20report%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFindings%20across%20such%20sites%20also%20challenge%20the%20idea%20that%20humans%20arrived%20in%20the%20Americas%20in%20one%20wave%20of%20migration%20over%20the%20Bering%20land%20bridge%2C%20according%20to%20Briana%20Pobiner%2C%20a%20co-author%20and%20paleoanthropologist%20at%20the%20Smithsonian%20Institution's%20National%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20History%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20likely%20that%20multiple%20waves%20of%20people%20came%20to%20Americas%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20according%20to%20The%20AP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiant%20ground%20sloths%20could%20reach%2013%20feet%20long%2C%20weighed%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20pounds%20and%20were%20equivalent%20in%20size%20to%20an%20Indian%20elephant.%20It%20walked%20on%20all%20fours%20and%20was%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20creatures%20in%20South%20America%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiant-sloth-artifacts-humans-reached-americas-earlier-than-thought-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689424247000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b28b24f9a2590019477298%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiant-sloth-artifacts-humans-reached-americas-earlier-than-thought-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20found%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20pendants%20in%20Brazil%2C%20dating%20from%20around%2025%2C000%20to%2027%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20were%20made%20from%20the%20now-extinct%20giant%20sloth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ashoaib%40insider.com%20(Alia%20Shoaib)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiant-sloth-artifacts-humans-reached-americas-earlier-than-thought-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20US%20consumer%20isn't%20in%20trouble.%20Here%20are%205%20stats%20that%20sho