8societies%20in%20flux%E2%80%99%20were%20not%20perhaps%20a%20better%20account%20of%20human%20history%20than%20what%20we%20normally%20get%20to%20read%2C%20%E2%80%98written%20by%20and%20for%20sedentary%20people.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20an%20interesting%20thought%2C%20as%20almost%20all%20of%20our%20families%20have%20migrated%20in%20the%20past%2C%20and%20many%20of%20us%20have%20also%20migrated%20at%20least%20once%20in%20our%20lifetime.%20Have%20we%20been%20seeing%20it%20all%20wrong%2C%20when%2C%20in%20truth%2C%20%E2%80%98motion%2C%20not%20stillness%2C%20is%20the%20universal%20norm%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20204px)%2085vw%2C%20204px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F15144042%2Fimage-1117-204x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22204%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F15144042%2Fimage-1117-204x300.png%20204w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F15144042%2Fimage-1117.png%20422w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663333%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMigrants%3A%20The%20Story%20of%20Us%20All%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Sam%20Miller%20(Abacus%2C%20February%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Remember%20that%20being%20sedentary%2C%20having%20a%20permanent%20home%20is%2C%20in%20deep%20historical%20terms%2C%20a%20relatively%20modern%20phenomenon%2C%20and%20that%20just%20four%20hundred%20years%20ago%20about%20a%20third%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20population%20was%20nomadic.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMiller%20admits%20that%20few%20migrants%20have%20it%20as%20good%20as%20he%20does.%20%E2%80%98I%20have%20had%20it%20easy.%20My%20passport%2C%20my%20job%2C%20my%20background%2C%20my%20colour%20and%20my%20gender%20all%20combine%20to%20make%20it%20uncomplicated%20for%20me%20to%20live%20almost%20anywhere%20I%20want%2C%20for%20long%20or%20short%20periods%2C%20in%20ways%20that%20most%20migrants%20never%20experience.%E2%80%99%20At%20no%20time%20in%20the%20book%20is%20Miller%20ever%20insensitive%20to%20what%20those%20less%20fortunate%20than%20him%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20instinct%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%20journalist%20is%20to%20look%20for%20the%20story%20behind%20it%20all%2C%20and%20throughout%20the%20book%20he%20keeps%20calling%20out%20injustices%20and%20atrocities%20that%20powerful%20migrants%20have%20visited%20upon%20the%20little%20people%20in%20so%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20But%20even%20so%20he%20still%20holds%20to%20a%20romantic%20notion%20of%20the%20migrant%20adventurer%2C%20and%20even%20wonders%20whether%20this%20wanderlust%20could%20be%20genetic%3A%20%E2%80%98And%2C%20indeed%2C%20there%20are%20some%20people%20who%20think%20a%20curiosity%20gene%20exists.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20identified%20it%2C%20a%20string%20of%20markers%20in%20our%20genome%20known%20as%20DRD4-7R%20%E2%80%93%20an%20ancient%20genetic%20mutation%20present%20on%20a%20significant%20scale%20in%20all%20human%20populations%2C%20but%20particularly%20prevalent%20in%20the%20first%20inhabitants%20of%20the%20Americas.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20appeal%20to%20deep%20history%20is%20where%20the%20book%20gets%20its%20%E2%80%98almost%E2%80%99%20quality%2C%20because%20%3Cem%3EMigrants%3A%20The%20Story%20of%20Us%20All%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20not%20meant%20as%20a%20rigorous%20study%20of%20migration%2C%20despite%20all%20the%20energy%20and%20research%20he%20invests%20into%20it.%20%E2%80%98My%20project%20and%20purpose%20is%20different.%20I%20am%20arguing%20that%20migration%2C%20forced%20and%20unforced%20and%20everything%20in%20between%2C%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20human%20experience%E2%80%A6%20If%20I%20were%20a%20philosopher%20I%20might%20go%20further%20at%20this%20point%2C%20and%20allow%20grand%20theories%20to%20take%20over%20from%20storytelling.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20waited%20for%20him%20to%20take%20further%20his%20observations%20about%20most%20of%20the%20migrants%20in%20his%20stories%20being%20male%2C%20something%20that%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20migration%20issue.%20Because%20%3Cem%3Ehis%3C%2Fem%3E%20eagerness%20to%20travel%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Emy%3C%2Fem%3E%20reluctance%20to%20move%2C%20though%20I%20do%20end%20up%20travelling%2C%20are%20probably%20linked%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%98surplus%E2%80%99%20men%20throughout%20history%20have%20migrated%20in%20search%20of%20lives%2C%20leaving%20behind%20womenfolk.%20Are%20young%20men%20routinely%20pushed%20out%20of%20the%20group%20the%20way%20young%20male%20gazelles%20are%20driven%20out%20of%20the%20herd%20by%20the%20alpha%20male%2C%20leaving%20them%20no%20option%20but%20to%20try%20their%20luck%20elsewhere%3F%20He%20was%20almost%20there%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-how-migration-shaped-our-nation-states%5C%22%3EBook%20Review%3A%20How%20Migration%20Shaped%20Our%20Nation%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%20in%20the%20book%2C%20when%20I%20was%20still%20making%20up%20my%20mind%20if%20I%20liked%20it%2C%20he%20declared%2C%20%3Cem%3Ea%20propos%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20so%20many%20groups%20claiming%20to%20be%20the%20Lost%20Tribes%20of%20Israel%2C%20that%20%E2%80%98everyone%20who%20has%20roots%20outside%20sub-Saharan%20Africa%20does%20have%20Middle%20Eastern%20ancestry.%20We%20now%20know%20from%20genetic%20evidence%20that%20all%20of%20these%20failed%20non-African%20contenders%20as%20possible%20Lost%20Tribes%20of%20Israel%20are%20of%20solid%20Middle%20Eastern%20stock%2C%20for%20their%20ancestors%20passed%20through%20the%20Middle%20East%20after%20modern%20humans%20left%20Africa%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20could%20he%20claim%20to%20have%20read%20Tony%20Joseph%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EEarly%20Indians%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Enot%20%3C%2Fem%3Eknow%20about%20the%20first%20successful%20migration%20out%20of%20Africa%2070%2C000%20years%20ago%20which%20went%20directly%20via%20the%20Horn%20of%20Africa%20to%20what%20is%20now%20Yemen%2C%20and%20onward%20to%20India%20and%20Australia%2C%20without%20going%20anywhere%20near%20the%20Middle%20East%3F%20I%20stopped%20to%20check%20the%20year%20of%20publication%20of%20%3Cem%3EMigrants%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%202023.%20In%20a%20book%20about%20migration%20this%20was%20a%20serious%20lapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20also%20had%20problems%20with%20the%20way%20he%20conflates%20all%20people%20who%20move%2C%20willingly%20or%20unwillingly%2C%20nomadic%20or%20just%20making%20one%20major%20shift%2C%20into%20a%20single%20group%3A%20migrants.%20Can%20one%20really%20lump%20together%20people%20making%20just%20the%20one%20move%20(and%20staying%20put%20thereafter)%20and%20groups%20who%20live%20perpetually%20as%20hunter-gatherer%20nomads%3F%20Isn%E2%80%99t%20there%20something%20bigger%20going%20on%2C%20a%20politics%20that%20forces%20sedentary%20people%20away%20from%20dangerous%20homelands%2C%20or%20traffics%20them%20across%20the%20Atlantic%20as%20part%20of%20the%20slave%20trade%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20scenarios%20don%E2%80%99t%20square%20with%20the%20almost%20na%C3%AFve%20ending%20of%20the%20book%3A%20%E2%80%98We%20also%20forget%20that%20we%20humans%20also%20migrate%20because%20we%20are%20bored%2C%20or%20curious%2C%20or%20adventurous%2C%20or%20enjoy%20a%20challenge%2C%20or%20because%20we%20wish%20to%20fulfil%20a%20dream.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20one%20gets%20past%20these%20theoretical%20hiccups%20one%20finds%20Miller%2C%20the%20journalist%2C%20sniffing%20out%20stories%20everywhere%2C%20things%20we%20had%20no%20idea%20of.%20The%20book%20is%20strewn%20with%20in-depth%20accounts%3A%20of%20the%20Vikings%20(and%20Viking%20Britain)%3B%20the%20Yaghan%20people%20of%20Tierra%20del%20Fuego%3B%20The%20Taino%20of%20the%20northern%20Caribbean%2C%20ruthlessly%20decimated%20by%20early%20Spanish%20settlers%3B%20Chinese%20migrants%20into%20the%20American%20West%20(and%20the%20stereotype%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98yellow%20peril%20incarnate%2C%20Dr.%20Fu%20Manchu%E2%80%99)%3B%20the%20West%20African%20slave%20trade%3B%20Mexican%20%3Cem%3Ebraceros%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecoming%20as%20migrant%20labour%20into%20California%3B%20Black%20Americans%20heading%20north%20(and%20even%20to%20Paris)%20leaving%20the%20American%20south%3B%20the%20Windrush%20story%20of%20Jamaican%20migrants%20to%20Britain%20(alongside%20the%20long%20and%20colourful%20prehistory%20of%20the%20ship%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEmpire%20Windrush%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20started%20out%20as%20a%20German%20ship%20ferrying%20Norwegian%20Jews%20to%20the%20death%20camps%20in%20Nazi%20Germany).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20stories%20are%20told%20with%20insight%20and%20empathy.%20Miller%20cries%20out%20against%20what%20we%20have%20come%20to%20%E2%80%93%20a%20world%20of%20borders%20and%20passports%20and%20immigration%20quotas%20which%20conspire%20to%20keep%20out%20poor%20non-white%20migrants%2C%20while%20celebrating%20rich%20white%20migrants%20as%20%E2%80%98expats%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMigrants%3A%20The%20Story%20of%20Us%20All%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20not%20the%20book%20I%20was%20expecting%20when%20I%20picked%20it%20up%2C%20but%20in%20the%20end%20I%20did%20like%20it%2C%20for%20the%20stories%20and%20insights%20in%20it%20that%20were%20new%20to%20me%20and%20Miller%E2%80%99s%20unfailing%20moral%20compass%20as%20he%20goes.%20With%20its%2011%20chapters%2C%20followed%20by%20short%20%E2%80%98Intermissions%E2%80%99%2C%20%3Cem%3EMigrants%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20pleasure%20to%20read%2C%20thought-provoking%20and%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20a%20welcome%20addition%20to%20the%20literature%20on%20human%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689414459000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F15150320%2Fimage-1119.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fin-a-